- Upper bound: \(\frac{2/3 - 0.5}{1/12} = \frac{1/6}{1/12} = 2\)

Thus, \(P(1/2 \leq \bar{X} \leq 2/3) = P(0 \leq Z \leq 2)\), where \(Z\) is a standard normal variable.

Using the standard normal distribution:
- \(P(Z \leq 2) \approx 0.97725\)
- \(P(Z \leq 0) = 0.5\)
- \(P(0 \leq Z \leq 2) = 0.97725 - 0.5 = 0.47725\)

