Problem: 6.3-5. Let $Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8$ be the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous-type distribution with 70 th percentile $\pi_{0.7}=27.3$.
(a) Determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The probability \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\) is equivalent to the probability that at least seven of the eight independent observations are less than 27.3, since \(Y_7\) is the seventh order statistic and the distribution is continuous. Given that the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\), the probability that a single observation is less than 27.3 is \(p = 0.7\).

Let \(K\) be the number of observations less than 27.3, so \(K \sim \text{Binomial}(n=8, p=0.7)\). Then:
\[
P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(K \geq 7) = P(K=7) + P(K=8).
\]

Calculate each term:
\[
P(K=7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,
\]
\[
P(K=8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = 1 \times (0.7)^8 \times 1.
\]

Compute \((0.7)^7 = 0.0823543\) and \((0.7)^8 = 0.05764801\):
\[
P(K=7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 8 \times 0.02470629 = 0.19765032,
\]
\[
P(K=8) = 0.05764801.
\]

Sum the probabilities:
\[
P(K \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833.
\]

Rounding to three significant figures gives 0.255. The unit is probability, so no additional unit is specified.

