The integral is evaluated using the beta function: \(\int_{0}^{1} x^3 (1 - x)^6  dx = B(4, 7) = \frac{\Gamma(4) \Gamma(7)}{\Gamma(11)}\). For integer values, \(\Gamma(k) = (k-1)!\), so:
- \(\Gamma(4) = 3! = 6\)
