**************
The solution calculates the energy of one mole of photons with a wavelength of 300 nm. After computing the energy per photon and scaling by Avogadro's number, the result is 399.0 kJ/mol. Considering significant figures (based on the wavelength having three significant figures), this is rounded to 399 kJ/mol. The comparison to the bond energy is part of the discussion but not the final numerical answer to extract.

